description.narrative: UNICEF, in collaboration with IOM and UNFPA, supported government in strengthening a multi-sectoral response mechanism for violence against children;and child marriage nationally and in the provinces of Nampula, Zambezia, Sofala and Manica. The Reference Group coordination mechanism chaired by the Prosecution Office coordinated violence against children;and trafficking responses both at provincial and district levels. The reporting mechanism in schools was piloted in 2021 with encouraging results and linkages to other services. UNICEF supported the Ministry of Education with the development of the multisectoral operational and monitoring and evaluation (M&E) plan of the violence against children;in school mechanism. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:12/01/2022
